403
00:18:28,460 --> 00:18:29,590
He colored his hair.

404
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:31,120
He fought.

405
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:33,380
He did everything

406
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:34,510
a teenage rebel did.

407
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:37,440
Back then,

408
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,570
my parents were busy

409
00:18:38,570 --> 00:18:39,770
and had no time for us.

410
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:43,180
They thought Cheng was a lost cause.

411
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:46,570
He once

412
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:49,160
smashed the headmaster's car at school.

413
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:49,840
The headmaster

414
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,640
wanted to talk to my parents.

415
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:54,190
Did you know what he told me?

416
00:18:55,380 --> 00:18:56,170
He said,

417
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:57,320
"That's great.

418
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:58,940
I can finally

419
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:00,080
talk to Dad alone."

420
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:03,290
Only then did I realize that

421
00:19:03,290 --> 00:19:04,480
he did these things

422
00:19:05,610 --> 00:19:06,380
to talk a bit more

423
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:07,440
to our father.

424
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:09,600
Did he get his way?

425
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,050
My father

426
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:14,730
still sent his assistant.

427
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,430
Why are you telling me this?

428
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:26,490
Can you tell Cheng

429
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:29,230
not to be a police officer anymore?

430
00:19:31,540 --> 00:19:32,330
Why?

431
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,900
He wanted to enter the police academy since childhood.

432
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:37,300
My parents disapproved.

433
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,400
He was rebellious.

434
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:41,060
My parents' disapproval

435
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:42,540
only gave further sustenance to him.

436
00:19:42,540 --> 00:19:43,340
He doesn't really want

437
00:19:43,340 --> 00:19:44,600
to be a police officer.

438
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:45,700
He just wants

439
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,680
our attention.

440
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:55,270
I think Du Cheng chooses to be a police officer

441
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:56,930
just for himself

442
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:58,680
and nobody else.

443
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:00,900
Du Cheng

444
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,610
is a man of great faith.

445
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:04,260
He believes

446
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:05,990
in his intuition and judgment.

447
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:09,260
He is uncompromising once he sets his mind.

448
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:10,700
No one

449
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,230
can manipulate his choice.

450
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:14,000
It's his nature

451
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:16,960
that made him a policeman.

452
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:19,180
I've lived with him

453
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:20,450
for thirty years,

454
00:20:21,380 --> 00:20:23,110
but I don't know him any better.

455
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:27,280
Perhaps

456
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:29,190
the depth of understanding

457
00:20:29,380 --> 00:20:30,170
